				 Equity rejig on CESC agenda
 A STAFF REPORTERCalcutta, Oct. 16: CESC Ltd aims to mop up about Rs 600 crore ($150 million) by issuing fresh equity shares.																								The issue proceeds will partially fund its proposed power projects in Haldia and Jharkhand. 																								Along with the equity issue, the company will extinguish same numbers of preference shares. A committee of directors of the company today decided to issue 2.825 crore new equity shares and extinguish the same number of preference shares that are part of the Rs 150-crore authorised capital of CESC. 																								The CESC promoters hold 50 lakh cumulative redeemable preference shares of Rs 10 each, bearing a fixed dividend of 16 per cent per annum. 																								A CESC source said the equities would be offered to some qualified institutional investors within few weeks. 																								CESC informed the Bombay Stock Exchange today that its board would consider at a later date on whether to raise the funds from the domestic or international markets. The company was also open to a private placement .																								As on September 30 this year, the company had a paid-up equity capital of Rs 84.32 crore. The company wants to raise its authorised share capital to Rs 150 crore from Rs 121.75 crore at present. This will be done by extinguishing the preference shares and issuing new shares.																								The board of directors is expected to meet at the end of this month and discuss the share restructuring plan through an amendment to the companys memorandum of association.																								CESC reported a substantial jump in net profit for the quarter ended June 2007. During the quarter, the profit grew 49.09 per cent to Rs 82 crore from Rs 55 crore in the same quarter last year. 																								The CESC stock today gained Rs 21.45, or 3.73 per cent, to close at Rs 596.65. 
